items.text: I take pride in completing tasks efficiently and on time.
items.rationale: Efficiency and timeliness are key aspects of the Executing factor.

items.text: When I start a project, I am determined to see it through to the end.
items.rationale: Determination and follow-through are central to Executing.

items.text: I enjoy creating detailed plans to achieve my goals.
items.rationale: Planning and goal achievement are core to Executing.

items.text: I am known for my ability to get things done.
items.rationale: Getting things done is a hallmark of the Executing factor.

items.text: I often take charge of tasks to ensure they are completed properly.
items.rationale: Taking charge to ensure task completion is indicative of Executing.

items.text: I prefer to work with a clear set of instructions and objectives.
items.rationale: Preference for clear instructions aligns with Executing.

items.text: I am meticulous about checking my work for errors.
items.rationale: Attention to detail and error-checking are part of Executing.

items.text: I feel satisfied when I can cross items off my to-do list.
items.rationale: Satisfaction from completing tasks is a trait of Executing.

items.text: I am driven by a strong sense of duty to complete my responsibilities.
items.rationale: A sense of duty and responsibility is central to Executing.

items.text: I often take the lead in organizing group projects.
items.rationale: Leadership in organization is a characteristic of Executing.

items.text: I am persistent in overcoming obstacles to achieve my goals.
items.rationale: Persistence in goal achievement is a key aspect of Executing.

items.text: I enjoy working on tasks that require a lot of focus and concentration.
items.rationale: Focus and concentration are important for Executing.

items.text: I like to ensure that everyone in the team is on the same page.
items.rationale: Ensuring team alignment can relate to Executing but also to Relationship Building.

items.text: I often find myself taking on more tasks than others.
items.rationale: Taking on tasks is related to Executing but could also indicate Influencing.

items.text: I enjoy motivating others to complete their tasks.
items.rationale: Motivating others can relate to Executing but also to Influencing.

items.text: I am skilled at persuading others to see my point of view.
items.rationale: Persuasion is a key component of the Influencing factor.

items.text: I often take the lead in group discussions.
items.rationale: Leading discussions is indicative of Influencing.

items.text: I enjoy speaking in front of large groups.
items.rationale: Public speaking is a hallmark of the Influencing factor.

items.text: I am often the one to rally the team towards a common goal.
items.rationale: Rallying a team is a characteristic of Influencing.

items.text: I am comfortable asserting my opinions in a group setting.
items.rationale: Asserting opinions is central to Influencing.

items.text: I like to inspire others with my vision for the future.
items.rationale: Inspiring others is a key aspect of Influencing.

items.text: I often find myself in leadership roles.
items.rationale: Leadership roles are indicative of Influencing.

items.text: I am adept at negotiating to achieve the best outcomes.
items.rationale: Negotiation skills are part of the Influencing factor.

items.text: I enjoy being the center of attention in social settings.
items.rationale: Enjoying attention is a trait of Influencing.

items.text: I am often the one to initiate conversations in a group.
items.rationale: Initiating conversations is a characteristic of Influencing.

items.text: I am skilled at convincing others to take action.
items.rationale: Convincing others is central to Influencing.

items.text: I like to challenge others to think differently.
items.rationale: Challenging others can relate to Influencing but also to Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I often find myself mediating conflicts between others.
items.rationale: Mediating conflicts can relate to Influencing but also to Relationship Building.

items.text: I enjoy building strong connections with others.
items.rationale: Building connections can relate to Influencing but also to Relationship Building.

items.text: I am known for my ability to connect with others on a personal level.
items.rationale: Personal connections are a key component of Relationship Building.

items.text: I enjoy helping others feel included and valued.
items.rationale: Inclusion and valuing others are central to Relationship Building.

items.text: I am often the one to organize social gatherings.
items.rationale: Organizing social events is indicative of Relationship Building.

items.text: I am skilled at resolving conflicts between friends.
items.rationale: Conflict resolution is a hallmark of Relationship Building.

items.text: I enjoy listening to others and understanding their perspectives.
items.rationale: Listening and understanding are key aspects of Relationship Building.

items.text: I often find myself supporting others in their personal growth.
items.rationale: Supporting personal growth is a characteristic of Relationship Building.

items.text: I am known for my empathy and compassion towards others.
items.rationale: Empathy and compassion are central to Relationship Building.

items.text: I enjoy creating a sense of community among my peers.
items.rationale: Creating community is a trait of Relationship Building.

items.text: I am often the one to offer emotional support to friends.
items.rationale: Offering emotional support is indicative of Relationship Building.

items.text: I am skilled at building trust with others.
items.rationale: Building trust is a key component of Relationship Building.

items.text: I enjoy being part of a team and working collaboratively.
items.rationale: Teamwork and collaboration are central to Relationship Building.

items.text: I like to ensure everyone feels heard in a group setting.
items.rationale: Ensuring others feel heard can relate to Relationship Building but also to Influencing.

items.text: I often find myself mediating between different viewpoints.
items.rationale: Mediating viewpoints can relate to Relationship Building but also to Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I enjoy leading teams to achieve common goals.
items.rationale: Leading teams can relate to Relationship Building but also to Influencing.

items.text: I am known for my ability to think several steps ahead.
items.rationale: Thinking ahead is a key component of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I enjoy analyzing complex problems to find solutions.
items.rationale: Problem analysis is central to Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I am skilled at identifying patterns and trends.
items.rationale: Pattern recognition is indicative of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I often find myself considering the long-term implications of decisions.
items.rationale: Considering long-term implications is a hallmark of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I enjoy brainstorming new ideas and possibilities.
items.rationale: Brainstorming is a key aspect of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I am often the one to propose innovative solutions.
items.rationale: Proposing innovations is a characteristic of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I am known for my ability to think critically about issues.
items.rationale: Critical thinking is central to Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I enjoy exploring different perspectives before making a decision.
items.rationale: Exploring perspectives is a trait of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I am skilled at synthesizing information from various sources.
items.rationale: Information synthesis is indicative of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I often find myself questioning assumptions and norms.
items.rationale: Questioning assumptions is a key component of Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I enjoy developing strategies to achieve complex goals.
items.rationale: Strategy development is central to Strategic Thinking.

items.text: I like to consider multiple scenarios before making a decision.
items.rationale: Considering scenarios can relate to Strategic Thinking but also to Executing.

items.text: I often find myself thinking about the future.
items.rationale: Future thinking can relate to Strategic Thinking but also to Influencing.

items.text: I enjoy collaborating with others to develop innovative ideas.
items.rationale: Collaboration for innovation can relate to Strategic Thinking but also to Relationship Building.
